# POPLOG

Poplog is an implementation of a prolog-style language lacking functions.
It has numbers, atoms, variables, and predicates, but it has no functions
as would be needed to evaluate say "X is 5+7."

# Installation

```
git clone https://github.com/joshrule/poplog.git  # clone the repository
cd poplog                                         # cd into the directory
cabal sandbox init                                # initialize sandbox
cabal install                                     # install the package
cabal repl                                        # launch ghci
ghci> :load src/examples/Main.hs                  # import the example repl
ghci> :main                                       # run the example
```